    "reasoning": "The task is to implement a 4-stage shift register using D flip-flops with active-low synchronous reset. The shift register should have 4 stages, meaning 4 DFFs connected in series. The reset is active-low, so when resetn is low, the register should be cleared to 0. All sequential logic must be triggered on the positive edge of clk. Since it's a shift register, on each clock cycle, the data should shift through the stages. We'll use 4 registers (logic [3:0]) to store the shifted values. The reset logic will set all registers to 0 when resetn is low. The input 'in' gets loaded into the first stage on each clock cycle, and the data shifts right through the stages. For the implementation, we will use a single always block for the sequential logic, with proper sensitivity list for the posedge clk and negedge resetn. To avoid syntax errors, I ensure all signals are declared as 'logic', use correct bit indexing, and follow SystemVerilog conventions.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input resetn,\n    input in,\n    output out\n);\n\n    // Register to hold the 4-stage shift register\n    logic [3:0] shift_reg;\n\n    // Sequential logic for the shift register\n    always @(posedge clk, negedge resetn) begin\n        if (!resetn)\n            shift_reg <= 4'b0;\n        else\n            shift_reg <= {shift_reg[2:0], in};\n    end\n\n    // Output is the last stage of the shift register\n    assign out = shift_reg[3];\n\nendmodule"
